'+*Description:*+

When users register cover assets in UST, the system performs Preflight Validation checks after an asset is uploaded. Each validation scenario should display a message consistent with the defined Registration Validation Worksheet, which lists all possible validation cases and their corresponding messages.

+*User Story:*+
*As a* user of UST,
*I want* the validation messages displayed during asset registration to exactly match the predefined messages in the Registration Validation Worksheet,
*so that* I receive consistent and clear feedback for any validation errors.

 

+*Acceptance Criteria:*+
 # Aspect Ratio Validation – Graphics, cover
    Given the asset’s media type is Graphics, asset type is cover, and configuration is Digital,
    When the Preflight Validation checks the Aspect Ratio,
    Then:
        If the Aspect Ratio is 1:1(square) , it should {color:#4c9aff}pass{color}, display {color:#ff0000}no validation message.{color}
        If the Aspect Ratio is not 1:1 (square), it should{color:#4c9aff} fail{color}, display : {color:#ff0000}The aspect ratio of this asset does not meet compliance. The image must be square. <br>+<Actual dimensions of submitted asset here> Please correct and resubmit.   Compliance guidelines can be found here: [https://mediaguide.sonymusic.com/graphics/cover-art/]{color}
        If the Aspect Ratio dimensions values are null (unable to calculate) , it should {color:#4c9aff}pass with warning{color}, display:
{color:#ff0000}The Value for this attribute is not readable from the header data of the submitted file. It is recommened to resave the asset(s) in a recent version of Adobe Photoshop to apply the appropriate header data and try again. Alternatively you can proceed as-is with the possibility that the file could fail secondary validations {color}

{color:#ff0000}           Given the asset’s media type is Graphics, asset type is cover, and configuration is physical,{color}
           When the Preflight Validation checks the Aspect Ratio,
{color:#172b4d}      {color}     {color:#172b4d}Then:{color}
{color:#172b4d}                   If the Aspect Ratio dimensions values are readable, it should {color}{color:#4c9aff}pass{color}{color:#172b4d}, display{color} {color:#de350b}no validation message.{color}
                  {color:#172b4d} If the Aspect Ratio dimensions values are null (unable to calculate) , it should {color}{color:#4c9aff}pass with warning{color}{color:#172b4d}, display:{color}
      {color:#de350b}  The Value for this attribute is not readable from the header data of the submitted file. It is recommened to resave the asset(s) in a recent version of Adobe Photoshop to apply the appropriate header data and try again. Alternatively you can proceed as-is with the possibility that the file could fail secondary validations {color}

2. Bits per channel/Bit depth Validation – Graphics, cover
    Given the asset’s media type is Graphics, asset type is cover, 
    When the Preflight Validation checks Bits per channel/Bit depth,
    Then:
        If Bits per channel/Bit depth is 8 bit or 16 bit, it should {color:#4c9aff}pass{color}, display {color:#de350b}no validation message.{color}
        If Bits per channel/Bit depth is NOT 8 bit or 16 bit, it should{color:#0747a6} {color:#4c9aff}fail{color}{color}, display : {color:#de350b}The bit depth of this asset does not meet compliance. The image must be 8 bit or 16 bit. Please correct and resubmit.   {color}
{color:#de350b}Compliance guidelines can be found here: https://mediaguide.sonymusic.com/graphics/cover-art/{color}
        If Bits per channel/Bit depth is null, it should{color:#4c9aff} pass with warning{color}, display: {color:#de350b}The Value for this attribute is not readable from the header data of the submitted file.  It is recommened to resave the asset(s) in a recent version of Adobe Photoshop to apply the appropriate header data and try again. {color}
{color:#de350b}Alternatively you can proceed as-is with the possibility that the file could fail secondary validations {color}

